{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Jt4FcbL5i6DFMVQSvQ12NA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task 2.5.2 is complete. The `parse_plan` state machine now walks lines once, tracking the current phase or bugs section, the current subsection within a phase, and a stack of open tasks by indent — opening/closing scopes on indent comparison just like mcloop's `parse`. `@deps` and `[RULEDOUT]` siblings are routed through the existing `_attach_*` helpers and accumulated on the parent task; task body classification (id, flag tags, action tag, annotations) is applied as each task line is consumed.\n\nFiles changed:\n- `bob_tools/planfile/parser.py`: added `_STAGE_RE` / `_BUGS_RE` / `_SUBSECTION_RE` / `_TASK_ID_RE`, the `_parse_phase_heading` / `_extract_task_id` / `_build_task` / `_current_scope_tasks` helpers, the `_TaskBuilder` / `_SubsectionBuilder` / `_PhaseBuilder` / `_BugsBuilder` mutable builder dataclasses, and a real implementation of `parse_plan`.\n- `bob_tools/planfile/tests/test_parser.py`: added `TestParsePlanStateMachine` with 13 tests covering empty input, phase/bugs/subsection scoping, indent-stack tree building, stack reset at section boundaries, body classification, `[RULEDOUT]` and `@deps` sibling routing, the rejected `## Phase phase_001:` form, orphan-task drop, and `source_path` pass-through.\n- `NOTES.md`: recorded the ambiguities the state machine had to resolve (orphan handling, subsections inside Bugs, keyword case normalization, stack reset at boundaries) for 2.5.4 / Stage 3 to revisit.\n\nAll four checks pass (ruff check, ruff format --check, pytest 303/303, mypy clean)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1509,"cache_read_input_tokens":140983,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1509},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},